        [
          "Higher Education",
          "Online Learning",
          "Collaborative Filtering",
          "Learning Materials",
          "25 students",
          "Not Applicable - students belong to Engineering in Foreign Languages School",
          "- Registration Form\n",
          "Learning Style is inferred from Questionnaire. \n\nSparsity problem → requires that there is at least one student with each learning tool to have selected a tool as preferrable. ",
          "The learning style is continuously updated based on the interactions of the user with the system.",
          "Similarity between items is computed using Jaccard Similarity.\n\nRepresentation of users used demographic data AND Learning Style as derived from the LS questionnaire. ",
          "Shortcuts: based on static information\n\nSuggestions: incorporate learning style and user interactions",
          "{Satisfaction: 12/20 students reported to be likely to use the recommendder again}",
          "Methodologically, the work can be summarized into 2 sections:\n\n1. Obtaining the learning styles from the questionnaire AND a rating of tools based on choices upon registration.\n\n2. Using a Collaborative Filtering approach to make recommendations.\n\nTo mitigate the sparsity problem, recommendation matrices are computed seaparately for each learning style.",
          "- Results on accuracy of LS evaluation or Recommendations is not reported.\n\n- Items whose score does not surpass a pre-determined threshold are never shown.\n\n- Cold-Start problem\n\n- Evaluation metrics considered (accuracy)\n\n- Survey evaluation for recommender based on sdatisfaction-"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
